task.summary: Refactoring of method names and code in general
Modified the events so they have a picker object with the interface "pick(list)" that returns an element, withdrawing it from the list. That way the pick criteria can be easily changed
Implemented Curse event (it doubles the victim percentage of the course's target. The caster steals half of the killing percentage

Modifications on the revive event (redistribution of all kill probabilities (might lose a bit of precision)
Fixes in Curse event
-Recalculation of victim probabilities -Fixing minor bugs in omedetoo -Refactoring

-Heavy refactoring ·New class IOKun (InputOutput-kun) in file "classes". ·Module "util" slipt into IOKun and module "constants". Only the most generic functions left there ·Refactored imports through all modules -Assasination event picks victim first and killer second
-InputKun to his own file -Every flavour list using InputKun -Colosseum doesn't read any files -Constants added for original flavour files
-Colosseum uses InputKun to read harpies, instead of opening the file in the Harpy_factorio of Arpio
-Added draw event. Same as kill, but without all that death!!
-Added OutputChan, for your output needs (log, queue tweets, and also tweeting
-Fixes in remote shait -Addition of a queue reading method in InputKun (returns a list with the tweet and the image path)

-Fixes in InputKun -Beginning to write the operation modes for the bot · Normal day (sensoo_wa_kawatta). Loads pickle (if any), executes an event and tweets about it · Queue processing. Tries to tweet the queued tweets. If successful, deletes them from the queue · Presentation. Initial tweets with the presentation of all the harpies.
-Updated Harpy innit to contemplate new fields
-Minor fixes -Differentiated in two methods. Tweet image (for normal tournament operation) and tweet text (for presentations or other propourses)
-Log and queue methods debugged -Changes in gitignore
-Fixes in the dequeueing -Fixes in the log and queue of the tweet -Removed stats from the kill event tweet -Refactoring in constants
-Corrections in Arpio (initialization of extra fields to none fixed) -Support for multipart tweets (more than 280 char) -New tests
-Reworked the event tweets so they include the handle (if any)
-Added the possibility of reloading flavour files (to update with more flavour mid execution)
